data.title: Diana Shipping Inc. reports Q4 2025 net income of $3.1 million, declares $0.01 dividend per common share.
data.description: In Athens, Greece, on February 26, 2026, Diana Shipping Inc. (NYSE: DSX), a global shipping company specializing in dry bulk vessels' ownership and bareboat charter-in, announced its financial results for the fourth quarter of 2025. The company reported a net income of $3.1 million, with net income attributable to common stockholders totaling $1.7 million. data.title: Telekom Srbija gets landmark credit ratings from Fitch & Moody’s, the 1st in Western Balkans, paving the way for international growth.
data.description: Telekom Srbija Group, based in Belgrade, Serbia, made history by becoming the first company in the Western Balkans to receive international credit ratings from Fitch Ratings and Moody’s Investors Service. Fitch Ratings confirmed Telekom Srbija’s long-term issuer rating following the company's inaugural issuance of bonds on the global financial market. The rating agencies recognized the Group’s robust market presence and resilience. This achievement showcases the Group’s financial strength and credibility on a global scale.
